When a foreigner gives birth in
Japan, within 30 days, they must

24
00:01:04,198 --> 00:01:08,803
apply for a residence permit with
the immigration bureau

25
00:01:09,103 --> 00:01:10,471
and report the birth

26
00:01:10,604 --> 00:01:12,606
to their country of origin
via the embassy or consulate.

27
00:01:34,662 --> 00:01:38,866
We're Millennials.
Got a Problem?

28
00:01:41,569 --> 00:01:43,137
Welcome.

29
00:01:43,671 --> 00:01:44,672
Oh.

30
00:01:45,473 --> 00:01:47,007
Sorry, I know today's
your day off.

31
00:01:47,141 --> 00:01:49,443
Anyway, what's going on?

32
00:01:49,577 --> 00:01:51,245
It's Maribu.
Right now he's...

33
00:01:53,013 --> 00:01:55,649
being detained at the Suginami
Police Station.

34
00:01:55,783 --> 00:01:58,152
I'm not allowed to see him so I'm
not clear on what happened.

35
00:01:58,285 --> 00:02:00,221
But it seems they'd run a
sting operation on his bar.

36
00:02:00,354 --> 00:02:01,355
You're under arrest.

37
00:02:01,489 --> 00:02:03,824
He's not involved anymore; he'd
gone clean. He's a gardener now.

38
00:02:03,924 --> 00:02:05,392
There was trouble at work.

39
00:02:05,526 --> 00:02:06,927
He skipped out and left.

40
00:02:07,027 --> 00:02:09,864
Then unfortunately, he got
caught by the police.

41
00:02:09,964 --> 00:02:11,866
His pub has a history of
victim complaints,

42
00:02:11,966 --> 00:02:14,635
and undercover agents had been
onto them for quite awhile now.

43
00:02:16,136 --> 00:02:18,939
What's going to happen to him?

44
00:02:19,006 --> 00:02:20,241
For intimidation...

45
00:02:20,341 --> 00:02:21,342
he'll get 2 years.

46
00:02:21,475 --> 00:02:23,978
And for attempted extortion, he'll
get under 10 years imprisonment.

47
00:02:24,078 --> 00:02:25,513
What?

48
00:02:25,646 --> 00:02:27,014
He just happened to be there.

49
00:02:27,147 --> 00:02:30,017
It seems the paperwork reflected
him to be the bar manager.

50
00:02:30,150 --> 00:02:31,352
Can the charges be dropped?

51
00:02:31,485 --> 00:02:33,687
Only an attorney
can answer that.

52
00:02:34,522 --> 00:02:35,823
Attorney...

53
00:02:38,425 --> 00:02:40,227
Attorney, eh...

54
00:02:40,828 --> 00:02:42,062
And his wife and child?

55
00:02:42,196 --> 00:02:44,732
Yamaji-san will
care for them...

56
00:02:45,866 --> 00:02:48,135
Yuka-san had "overstayed."

57
00:03:03,017 --> 00:03:04,118
Then, the attorney...

58
00:03:04,218 --> 00:03:06,053
We have to find one fast.

59
00:03:06,186 --> 00:03:07,888
I'm on it already.

60
00:03:08,022 --> 00:03:08,822
Who is it?

61
00:03:08,923 --> 00:03:12,359
I've found one, I've found one.
Shut up, for crying out loud...

62
00:03:12,493 --> 00:03:13,727
"Shut up"?

63
00:03:15,362 --> 00:03:17,231
By the way, though the
timing is odd...

64
00:03:18,032 --> 00:03:20,201
I heard you're getting married,
congratulations.

65
00:03:20,301 --> 00:03:22,002
Congratulations.

66
00:03:22,102 --> 00:03:23,137
Nothing's happened yet...

67
00:03:23,270 --> 00:03:25,239
Akane-chan was elated; she said
she's a chairman's wife.

68
00:03:25,339 --> 00:03:27,241
So, your older brother
is becoming a farmer?

69
00:03:27,341 --> 00:03:29,176
- Shut up, for crying out loud.
- "Shut up"?

70
00:03:29,310 --> 00:03:32,513
"Maternity Handbook"
- We've got good news of our own.

71
00:03:34,214 --> 00:03:35,783
Which means...

72
00:03:35,883 --> 00:03:38,886
The 6th generation heir will still
be my older brother.

73
00:03:39,386 --> 00:03:41,055
Midori-san is the wife of the
chairman...

74
00:03:42,022 --> 00:03:43,190
it seems.

75
00:03:44,358 --> 00:03:46,226
I'm just his supporter.

76
00:03:46,860 --> 00:03:48,028
I see.

77
00:03:48,095 --> 00:03:51,932
Do you want to reconsider quit-
ting, and go back to work?

78
00:03:52,933 --> 00:03:54,068
Why?

79
00:03:56,003 --> 00:03:57,004
Why? Because...

80
00:03:57,137 --> 00:04:00,074
I'm not marrying you because you
might become a chairman.

81
00:04:00,474 --> 00:04:05,379
If you're going to support your
brother, then your supporter

82
00:04:05,512 --> 00:04:07,047
will be your wife's role.

83
00:04:07,648 --> 00:04:12,019
I quit my job because I found some-
thing better than work. That's all.

84
00:04:21,729 --> 00:04:23,430
Can I take this frying pan?

85
00:04:24,031 --> 00:04:25,299
It's light and easy to use.

86
00:04:25,432 --> 00:04:26,533
Just buy a new one.

87
00:04:26,634 --> 00:04:28,602
No, I want this one.

88
00:04:28,736 --> 00:04:32,640
All right then, go ahead.
You can have it.

89
00:04:33,107 --> 00:04:34,508
I dunno, that's kinda cute.

90
00:04:34,642 --> 00:04:36,343
She is kinda cute.

91
00:04:36,477 --> 00:04:38,345
She said she was having
marriage "pink."

92
00:04:38,479 --> 00:04:40,614
It'll eventually turn blue...

93
00:04:40,714 --> 00:04:42,816
We'll both be unemployed
starting next month.

94
00:04:42,950 --> 00:04:45,319
Too bad you can't be chairman.

95
00:04:45,452 --> 00:04:47,821
Aso-san is late.
Our meeting is at 3:00.

96
00:04:47,921 --> 00:04:49,156
Maybe he's already here.

97
00:04:49,256 --> 00:04:50,357
Huh? The attorney?

98
00:04:50,891 --> 00:04:51,692
Huh?

99
00:04:51,825 --> 00:04:55,929
There and the major contractor
Hayama Steel?

100
00:04:56,030 --> 00:04:59,033
Your companies have a close
business relationship, don't you?

101
00:04:59,433 --> 00:05:00,234
Therefore...

102
00:05:00,367 --> 00:05:02,002
Crap, crap, he's coming.

103
00:05:02,102 --> 00:05:04,004
There's nothing the police
can do. Ice coffee.

104
00:05:04,104 --> 00:05:05,406
Yes.

105
00:05:06,006 --> 00:05:07,241
Seriously...

106
00:05:08,308 --> 00:05:10,277
Howdy.

107
00:05:10,411 --> 00:05:12,613
I overslept, so...

108
00:05:12,713 --> 00:05:15,449
Evidence that can't be presented
is not evidence.

109
00:05:17,017 --> 00:05:18,018
Seriously.

110
00:05:20,154 --> 00:05:21,155
What? What?

111
00:05:21,255 --> 00:05:24,358
So he is... is he?

112
00:05:24,491 --> 00:05:25,659
Oh, yes.

113
00:05:25,759 --> 00:05:28,962
He is my son...

114
00:05:29,063 --> 00:05:32,533
I told you didn't I?
He's an attorney.

115
00:05:32,633 --> 00:05:34,234
What?

116
00:05:35,102 --> 00:05:38,439
Did you get a tan,
Masanobu-kun?

117
00:05:38,772 --> 00:05:40,507
Riding the waves?

118
00:05:40,641 --> 00:05:43,811
Ouch, ouch, ouch...

119
00:05:45,646 --> 00:05:48,015
I only have 4 minutes to spare.
Please make it brief.

120
00:05:48,882 --> 00:05:51,485
First, I need a retainer
of 300,000 yen.

121
00:05:51,618 --> 00:05:54,254
For winning the case, I will
expect another 300,000 yen.

122
00:05:54,388 --> 00:05:56,056
Of course, expenses are
charged separately.

123
00:05:56,190 --> 00:05:59,259
Wait a second. You're asking his
brother to defend him?

124
00:05:59,393 --> 00:06:01,061
It'll depend on the
agreement.

125
00:06:01,495 --> 00:06:04,064
You were late to the appointment,
which lowers my opinion of you.

126
00:06:05,099 --> 00:06:06,900
I mean, seriously.

127
00:06:07,034 --> 00:06:09,803
You haven't called in ages, and
suddenly this is the call I get?

128
00:06:09,937 --> 00:06:12,306
What kind of father are you?

129
00:06:12,439 --> 00:06:13,240
Please...

130
00:06:13,340 --> 00:06:15,008
When's the last time
I saw you?

131
00:06:19,012 --> 00:06:20,681
It's not funny.

132
00:06:22,349 --> 00:06:23,817
The time...

133
00:06:25,018 --> 00:06:25,853
to...

134
00:06:25,986 --> 00:06:27,221
Seat for 4 people.

135
00:06:27,354 --> 00:06:28,856
expose my darkness
has come.

136
00:06:28,989 --> 00:06:32,559
Here? That's a problem.
Go do that in the booth.

137
00:06:32,693 --> 00:06:34,428
When Masanobu
was four...

138
00:06:34,862 --> 00:06:36,263
after I had a big affair...

139
00:06:36,396 --> 00:06:38,232
I married for the second time.

140
00:06:39,633 --> 00:06:40,868
And...

141
00:06:41,101 --> 00:06:44,438
that was... to Hitomi.

142
00:06:47,107 --> 00:06:49,009
She's Maribu's mother.

143
00:06:50,511 --> 00:06:51,578
Huh?

144
00:06:51,678 --> 00:06:54,114
He wouldn't remember anything
if he was only four.

145
00:06:54,214 --> 00:06:56,450
The child wouldn't, but...

146
00:06:58,018 --> 00:07:00,220
the mother would ponder.

147
00:07:00,354 --> 00:07:04,191
A step-child and her own
child are utterly different.

148
00:07:04,324 --> 00:07:08,095
She tried to raise them equally,
without favouritism...

149
00:07:08,228 --> 00:07:09,897
and that's what got her stressed.

150
00:07:10,030 --> 00:07:12,866
For example, in a running race at
the school sports event,

151
00:07:12,966 --> 00:07:14,601
Masanobu came in 2nd place.

152
00:07:14,735 --> 00:07:18,338
As his mother she wanted
Maribu to also come in 2nd place.

153
00:07:18,472 --> 00:07:20,741
Or 1st place,

154
00:07:20,841 --> 00:07:26,780
and simultaneously, she rued her
ego for having wished that.

155
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:29,183
Yet, 3rd place would
have been unacceptable.

156
00:07:29,316 --> 00:07:30,484
3rd place is no fun.

157
00:07:30,617 --> 00:07:35,222
So only 2nd place for both would've
satisfied her sense of equality.

158
00:07:35,889 --> 00:07:41,061
Therefore when he came in 2nd,
she would say in relief...

159
00:07:41,195 --> 00:07:42,896
"I'm so glad."

160
00:07:43,463 --> 00:07:46,700
"Masanobu, Maribu, both of
you did great."

161
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:49,036
And because of those words...

162
00:07:49,403 --> 00:07:52,339
Masanobu was deeply hurt.

163
00:07:52,473 --> 00:07:54,341
- Why?
- Refill.

164
00:07:54,474 --> 00:07:55,909
One highball coming up.

165
00:07:56,009 --> 00:08:00,514
Because he was equally praised
when the situation wasn't equal.

166
00:08:01,515 --> 00:08:04,484
"Masanobu you did great!
Maribu you did great too."

167
00:08:04,618 --> 00:08:06,019
That would've been fine.

168
00:08:06,820 --> 00:08:10,490
But to say Masanobu and Maribu
both did great, is not.

169
00:08:10,591 --> 00:08:12,159
How confusing.

170
00:08:12,259 --> 00:08:15,095
Huh? What?

171
00:08:15,229 --> 00:08:16,430
You see...

172
00:08:16,930 --> 00:08:21,068
what took away that
confusion was...

173
00:08:21,201 --> 00:08:22,069
Millennial education.

174
00:08:22,202 --> 00:08:23,637
Exactly.

175
00:08:24,238 --> 00:08:26,573
"Only one"
instead of "number one."

176
00:08:26,673 --> 00:08:29,810
That's right. You can't tell who's
1st in those school races anyway.

177
00:08:29,943 --> 00:08:33,013
Teachers with flags run along
with them to mix it all up.

178
00:08:35,349 --> 00:08:39,186
I wish millennial education had
been applied much sooner.

179
00:08:40,420 --> 00:08:43,023
What? What is it?

180
00:08:43,090 --> 00:08:47,594
I was thinking I'd met
your wife somewhere.

181
00:08:47,728 --> 00:08:49,029
This.

182
00:08:49,129 --> 00:08:51,265
-You mind?
-Go ahead.

183
00:08:58,505 --> 00:08:59,940
What?

184
00:09:00,307 --> 00:09:02,509
That's Aso Hitomi.

185
00:09:02,643 --> 00:09:03,443
Right?

186
00:09:03,577 --> 00:09:07,047
Ah, my secret has been revealed.

187
00:09:07,180 --> 00:09:08,382
She's a "Tama Beauty."

188
00:09:08,515 --> 00:09:10,284
I've been a subscriber.

189
00:09:10,384 --> 00:09:13,253
I get a free poster
every year.

190
00:09:16,723 --> 00:09:18,659
So Aso is...

191
00:09:18,759 --> 00:09:20,527
the same "Aso" as Aso Hitomi.

192
00:09:20,661 --> 00:09:21,528
I'm humbled
to say, yes.

193
00:09:21,662 --> 00:09:23,597
She used the name instead
of her maiden name.

194
00:09:23,730 --> 00:09:24,932
To not vex her kids.

195
00:09:25,032 --> 00:09:26,733
Gosh I was a fan.

196
00:09:26,867 --> 00:09:29,736
She debuted as a heroine
in a morning drama.

197
00:09:29,870 --> 00:09:30,938
That was "Kappore-chan."

198
00:09:31,004 --> 00:09:32,239
Right, "Kappore-chan"!

199
00:09:32,339 --> 00:09:33,573
You know your stuff.

200
00:09:33,674 --> 00:09:37,277
But just when her career was
taking off, she got married

201
00:09:37,411 --> 00:09:40,948
to some bubble-refugee flim-flam
real-estate jerk.

202
00:09:42,482 --> 00:09:43,717
I should punch
you for that.

203
00:09:43,850 --> 00:09:45,218
Hey Nakamori-kun.

204
00:09:45,352 --> 00:09:46,853
When was that posted?

205
00:09:47,154 --> 00:09:49,423
I dunno; I think
it's always been there.

206
00:09:51,591 --> 00:09:53,226
As I thought.

207
00:09:53,927 --> 00:09:56,363
He's been coming here
to see his mother.

208
00:09:56,463 --> 00:09:57,864
Maribu-kun.

209
00:09:58,598 --> 00:09:59,399
Here.

210
00:10:09,609 --> 00:10:13,981
And the older brother
began to bully his little brother...

211
00:10:14,047 --> 00:10:16,116
because he was envious
of him.

212
00:10:16,783 --> 00:10:22,422
He played the part of the kind older
brother in front of their mother...

213
00:10:23,223 --> 00:10:24,658
but behind her back,

214
00:10:25,659 --> 00:10:28,929
he bullied Maribu.
She didn't notice it.

215
00:10:29,029 --> 00:10:30,630
This so-called
"Tama Beauty."

216
00:10:31,198 --> 00:10:33,433
It seems she pretended not
to see what she saw.

217
00:10:33,567 --> 00:10:35,035
"It seems"?

218
00:10:35,135 --> 00:10:36,970
What were you doing, then?
You're the father you know.

219
00:10:37,838 --> 00:10:39,439
Masanobu had...

220
00:10:39,773 --> 00:10:43,677
started law school at the
public university...

221
00:10:44,177 --> 00:10:49,483
And Maribu was getting
his own life started...

222
00:10:49,616 --> 00:10:51,818
Um... My...

223
00:10:52,486 --> 00:10:54,921
How do I say it...

224
00:10:55,022 --> 00:10:59,726
My adultery got found out...

225
00:10:59,860 --> 00:11:01,228
What are you thinking?

226
00:11:02,195 --> 00:11:06,867
Tama Beauty went
crazy with rage.

227
00:11:06,967 --> 00:11:09,302
She had a lot of
pride to begin with.

228
00:11:09,703 --> 00:11:12,939
She always condemned my
character after that.

229
00:11:13,006 --> 00:11:14,841
You reaped what you'd sowed.

230
00:11:20,881 --> 00:11:23,517
- You know, Yamaji-san...
- Yeah?

231
00:11:23,650 --> 00:11:25,218
I...

232
00:11:25,819 --> 00:11:29,022
"you reaped what you've
sowed" is...

233
00:11:29,556 --> 00:11:34,061
of all the many phrases, the one
I hate the most.

234
00:11:34,194 --> 00:11:36,596
- Sorry.
- The most, without question.

235
00:11:36,730 --> 00:11:38,265
2nd is: "legal compensation,"
3rd is: "alimony."

236
00:11:38,398 --> 00:11:41,435
- But the fact is...
- I reaped what I'd sowed.

237
00:11:42,202 --> 00:11:45,839
I admit that, of course I do.

238
00:11:45,972 --> 00:11:48,975
I'll live the rest of my life
reaping what I've sowed.

239
00:11:49,076 --> 00:11:50,510
So don't remind me.

240
00:11:50,644 --> 00:11:52,646
You know, don't mention it.

241
00:11:52,779 --> 00:11:56,016
Don't mention it on the side.
Give it to me as a big conclusion.

242
00:11:56,149 --> 00:11:57,284
A big conclusion.

243
00:11:57,384 --> 00:11:58,785
Or...

244
00:11:58,885 --> 00:12:02,155
tell me after I'm dead.

245
00:12:02,255 --> 00:12:03,757
Because I know...

246
00:12:04,357 --> 00:12:06,693
my death won't be dignified any way.

247
00:12:08,895 --> 00:12:09,963
You laughed, didn't you?

248
00:12:11,465 --> 00:12:15,902
After the divorce Masanobu became
estranged to me.

249
00:12:16,002 --> 00:12:18,238
He had no obligation
to live with me,

250
00:12:18,338 --> 00:12:21,274
so he left home and pursued
to become a lawyer.

251
00:12:22,109 --> 00:12:27,814
Maribu was touted as a prodigy, but
at that time, his grades plummeted.

252
00:12:28,048 --> 00:12:33,086
That was because the diffused
attention he had been receiving

253
00:12:33,220 --> 00:12:35,822
from his mom suddenly
honed in on him and him alone.

254
00:12:38,225 --> 00:12:43,029
"I didn't marry to put a stranger's
child through college."

255
00:12:43,864 --> 00:12:46,032
"Your turn has finally come."

256
00:12:46,099 --> 00:12:49,536
"You must boldly aim for the top."

257
00:12:49,636 --> 00:12:51,571
"What do you think you're doing?"

